 Emergency workers surrounded the Delta Air Lines plane at LaGuardia Airport after an odor of smoke was reported by the crew moments after Flight 2522 .
Passengers were still on board as firefighters walked through the cabin with a thermal imaging camera to locate a potential heat source .
After the plane landed a firefighter used a thermal camera camera to smoke a potential source .
Passenger Pamela says passengers were kept on the plane for about 45 minutes .